In England, in the seven days to 20 November, there were 242,349 new confirmed cases (428.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 November, there were 218,759 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 11% (23,590 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 25 November is 8,496,990 (15,025.6 cases per 100,000 population).
